## 6. Platform Semantics (Stable Runtime Behavior)

These points come from MuleSoft’s Scheduler documentation and change rarely:

| Topic | Behavior |
|---|---|
| **Timezone** | Scheduler uses the **JVM/host** timezone **except CloudHub**, where it runs in **UTC** unless **`cron` `timeZone`** overrides. |
| **Cluster / multi-worker** | Scheduler runs on **one** node only — the **primary** in a cluster; not every worker fires independently. |
| **Back-pressure** | If the runtime cannot allocate resources for a trigger, that execution may be **skipped** (see execution engine back-pressure docs). |
| **Cron engine** | Expressions are **Quartz**-compatible; field order: seconds, minutes, hours, day-of-month, month, day-of-week, optional year — plus Quartz special characters (`* ? - , / L W #`). |
| **Minimum processors** | A flow whose only source is `<scheduler>` **must** have at least one additional processor after it. |

---

## 7. Checklist — Before Marking Job Work Complete

- [ ] **`JOBS.md`** updated (not `API.md`) with schedule keys, sources, sinks, logic, manual path, ops notes.
- [ ] **`config.yaml`** holds all cadence values; XML uses **`${...}`** only.
- [ ] Scheduled flow starts with **`<scheduler>`**; business logic in **sub-flow**; **manual HTTP** flow calls the same sub-flow.
- [ ] **No `vars.httpStatus`** / HTTP-oriented error mapping on job paths.
- [ ] **Error handler** logs ERROR + DLQ/email (or documented interim logger-only).
- [ ] **Object Store** watermark pattern documented; retrieve uses **`target`** + default; store uses **`failIfPresent` / `failOnNullValue`** as appropriate.
- [ ] **`smoke-test.ps1`** includes the manual trigger case(s); **`PROJECT_CONTEXT.md`** updated.
- [ ] **Salesforce (or similar):** for **high-volume** loads, **`JOBS.md`** / **`PROJECT_CONTEXT.md`** reflects **batched** or **chunked (≤200)** DML/query (or delta) — not **only** per-row `foreach` DML without a documented trade-off (see **`mule-salesforce.mdc`** §4).

